In the **Choose whether to enable route services** section, choose either **Enable route services** or **Disable route services**. Route services are a class of marketplace services that perform filtering or content transformation on app requests and responses. For more information, see [Route Services](../services/route-services.html) and the [List Marketplace Services](../devguide/services/managing-services.html#marketplace) section of the _Managing Service Instances with the cf CLI_ topic.
See the [Route Services](../services/route-services.html) topic for details. 
	1. If you enabled route services, you can also configure the **Bypass security checks for route service lookup** field. Pivotal recommends that you do not enable this field because it has potential security concerns. However, you may need to enable it if your load balancer requires mutual TLS from clients. For more information, see [Configuring Route Service Lookup](route-service-lookup.html). 